            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The declarations in `cpython/array.pxd` expose the internals of the array implementation in CPython. The only advice I can give you here is: if you need your code to support PyPy, then don't use C level access to the `array.array` data type. That's essentially just saying: if you need portability, don't write non-portable code.\r\n\r\nYou could try to get away with using the `array` type through a memoryview, but I can't say how well supported (and efficient) that is in PyPy.",
            "created_at": "2018-07-07T14:23:08Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/1818#issuecomment-403219131",
